        <p>
            It is important that women with MS should be offered all relevant health screening, for example 
            for cervical and breast cancer<sup>103</sup>. Women should be asked if they are up to date with their 
            screening programmes and are able to access the tests as women with chronic disabling conditions 
            may face substantial barriers that limit health promoting activities critical to a healthy life.
        </p>

